    "body": "Hi @xiaozhu001, I translated your message [on Google Translate](https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=auto&tl=en&u=https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/issues/2433). If you could write in English it would be appreciated.\r\n\r\n`_setupRole` is meant to be used in the constructor only. We can't stop people from using it elsewhere. However, all roles can be audited via the events emitted by the contract. Auditing of the code + monitoring of events can be put in place to prevent the kind of problem that you describe. Admin roles (that can revoke other roles) should be highly secured accounts in cold storage.",
